// INC-35 iq2_s x q8_K byte-exact HW validation harness (ssh rvv, -march=rv64gcv).
//
// Proves: the C our compiler emits for the new tcrv_rvv.iq2_s_q8_k_block_dot op (the
// COMPLETE ggml ggml_vec_dot_iq2_s_q8_K GRID-codebook super-block kernel) computes the
// SAME fp32 result *s as ggml's OWN _generic iq2_s reference, BIT-FOR-BIT (memcmp of the
// float bits), over random block_iq2_s x block_q8_K arrays at n multiples of 256 + named
// edge cases (grid index range into [512,1023] via the qh-bit plane, sign patterns,
// scale extremes incl distinct ls1/ls2, q8 +/-127). FOUR negative controls (a WRONG grid
// + WRONG explicit signs + WRONG scale-bias + a WRONG qh-bit injection) must FAIL ->
// proves the 1024-grid lookup, the EXPLICIT sign region, the explicit scale array, AND
// the qh 2-bit high-index injection are the live, load-bearing mechanisms.
//
// iq2_s is the SIBLING of iq2_xs -- the THIRD member of the deep IQ tail. It REUSES the
// GRID + sign mechanism with THREE structural deltas vs iq2_xs: a 1024-entry grid, a
// 10-bit index assembled from a single qs index byte plus 2 qh-plane bits
// (idx = qs[l] | ((qh[ib32] << (8-2*l)) & 0x300)), and EXPLICIT signs read DIRECTLY from
// a sign-byte region inside qs[64] (signs = qs+32, NO ksigns lookup).
//
// REFERENCE: ggml's VERBATIM _generic (quants.c:947-997): d = fp16(x.d)*y.d; signs =
// qs+QK_K/8; for each of 8 sub-blocks, ls1/ls2 from x.scales[ib32]; two halves {0,1}
// scaled by ls1, {2,3} by ls2; per group grid = (uint8*)(iq2s_grid + (qs[l] | ((qh[ib32]
// << (8-2*l)) & 0x300))), sumi += q8[j]*grid[j]*(signs[l]&kmask?-1:1); bsum += ls*sumi;
// sumf += d*bsum; *s = 0.125f*sumf. FP16->FP32 mirrors the board's scalar _Float16
// widening (lossless). Whole TU built with the same -ffp-contract.
//
// The kernel under test is the UNMODIFIED, compiler-emitted iq2_s kernel
// (iq2_s_emitted.cpp) -- every line tagged source_op=tcrv_rvv.iq2_s_q8_k_block_dot.

